gurmukhi: ਅੈਸੀ ਗੁਨ ਸਾਗਰ ੳੁਜਾਗਰ ਸੁ ਨਾਗਰ ਹੈ ਲੀਨੋ ਮਨ ਮੇਰੋ ਹਰਿ ਨੈਨ ਕੋਰ ਚਿਤ ਹੀ ||੮੯||
transliteration: Aisoo Goun Saagad Ujaagad Su Naagad Hai Loono Man Mero Har(i0 Nain Kor Chit Hoo||89||
translation: “That most beautiful damsel hath manifested herself and the ocean of suchlike qualities; she hath captivated my mind with the sharpness of her eyes.”89.

gurmukhi: ਬਾਤ ਦੈਤ ਕੀ ਸੁੰਭ ਸੁਨਿ ਬੋਲਿਓ ਕਛੁ ਮੁਸਕਾਤ ||
transliteration: Baat Dait Koo Sounbh Soun(i) Bolio Kachh(u) Mouskaat||
translation: Hearing the words of the demon, the king Sumbh said smilingly;

gurmukhi: ਚਤੁਰ ਦੂਤ ਕੋੳੂ ਭੇਜੀੲੇ ਲਖਿ ਅਾਵੈ ਤਿਹ ਘਾਤ ||੯੦||
transliteration: Chatur Doot Ko( i)  Bhajooe Lakh(i0 Aavai Tih Ghaat||90||
translation: “Some expert spy be sent there in order to know her ingenuity.”90.

gurmukhi: ਬਹੁਰਿ ਕਹੀ ੳੁਨ ਦੈਤ ਅਬ ਕੀਜੈ ੲੇਕ ਬਿਚਾਰ ||
transliteration: Bahur(i) Kahoo Oun Dait Ab Koojai Ek Bichaar||
translation: That demon said again, “It may now be considered;

gurmukhi: ਜੋ ਲਾੲਿਕ ਭਟ ਸੈਨ ਮੈ ਭੇਜਹੁ ਦੈ ਅਧਿਕਾਰ ||੯੧||
transliteration: Jo Laaik Bhat Sain Mai Bhejoh Dai Adhikaar||91||
translation: “To send the most efficient warrior in the army giving him authority.”91.

gurmukhi: ਬੈਠੋ ਹੁਤੋ ਨ੍ਰਿਪ ਮੱਧਿ ਸਭਾ ੳੁਠਿ ਕੈ ਕਰਿ ਜੋਰਿ ਕਹਿਓ ਮਮ ਜਾੳੂਂ ||
transliteration: Baitho Houto Nrip Maddh(i) Sabhaa Outh(i) Kai Kar(i) Jor(i) Kahio Mam Jaaoon||
translation: The king was seated in his court and there with folded hands (Dhumar Lochan) said, I will go;

gurmukhi: ਬਾਤਨ ਤੇ ਰਿਝਵਾੲਿ ਮਿਲਾੲਿਹੋਂ ਨਾਤਰਿ ਕੇਸਨ ਤੇ ਗਹਿ ਲਿਅਾੳੁਂ ||
transliteration: Baatan Te Rijhvaae Milaaehon Naatar(i) Kesan Te Gad(i) Liaaoon||
translation: “Firstly, I shall please her with talk, otherwise, I shall bring her, seizing her by her hair;

gurmukhi: ਕ੍ਰੋਧ ਕਰੈ ਤਬ ਜੁੱਧ ਕਰੋਂ ਰਣ ਸ੍ਰੳੁਣਤ ਕੀ ਸਰਤਾਨ ਬਹਾੳੂਂ ||
transliteration: Kruddh Darai Tah Juddh Daron Ran Sraounai Koo Sartaan Bahaaoon||
translation: “If she makes me furious, I shall wage the war with her and cause the steams of blood to flow in the battlefield;

gurmukhi: ਲੋਚਨਧੂੰਮ ਕਹੈ ਬਲ ਅਾਪਨੋ ਸ੍ਵਾਸਨ ਸਾਥ ਪਹਾਰ ੳੁਡਾੳੂਂ ||੯੨||
transliteration: Lochanndhoonm Kahai Bal Aapno Svaasan Saath Pahaar Udaaoon||92||
translation: “I have so much strength that I can make the mountains fly with the blowing of my breaths,” said Dhumar Lochan.92.

gurmukhi: ੳੁਠੇ ਬੀਰ ਕੋ ਦੇਖ ਕੈ ਸੁੰਭ ਕਹੀ ਤੁਮ ਜਾਹੁ ||
transliteration: Outhe Boor Ko Dekh Kai Sounbh Kahoo Toum Jaahu||
translation: Seeing that warrior getting up, Sumbh told him to go:
